<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 02 at 12:22AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern Texas
County through 1245 AM CDT...
At 1221 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles west of Tyrone, or 14 miles southwest of Liberal, moving
northeast at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Tyrone.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
